{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Hold a referendum on using Alternative Vote (AV) for general elections",
        "additional_details": "We think the the AV system produces better representation of the people.\r\n \r\nIn the AV system, you pick candidates in order of preference. If your first choice is knocked out your vote goes to the second and so on.\r\n \r\nThis means your vote can still count even if your first choice wasn\u2019t popular enough to win. We think this better represents the feelings of the nation and its people and parties must compromise in the interest of all.\r\n",
        "background": "It has been more than a decade since we were last given the chance to change the way we vote. We think it\u2019s time we got better representation in Parliament and that the current system has produced only chaos, where two parties rule.",
